    INSERT INTO story(id, title, issue_id, synopsis, reprint_notes, notes, type_id) VALUES(53840,"Case of the Valiant Dog", 5053,"General Darnell is wounded when gangsters raid his office and a dog prevents the Police from catching the crooks. Wonder Woman saves the dog from being killed by the Police and soon discovers that the dog recognized one of the crooks: Sandy's father who has lost his memory and is driving for the gangsters.",NULL,"Joyce Murchison verified to Jerry Bails.Credits verified by Joyce Murchison to Jerry Bails. Jill Lepore does NOT reflect the Marston credit originally listed along with Joyce Murchison credit. According to her book below Jill talked with Joye about her credits and she did not likewise give the Marston credit (like she did for the story in Sensation #55 for example) so it has been removed (by Craig Delich). Joye Hummel is the maiden name for the scripter (before 1947) then she married David Murchison. When he passed away Joye married Jack Kelly. So her name all combined reads Joye Hummel Murchison Kelly the way Jill Lapore refers to her in her book \"The Secret History of Wonder Woman\" (2014). Rex is not the name of the dog in Rex The Wonder Dog series.",19
